1. Download and install VS Code and NodeJS

2. Open the project in VS Code and change the directory to the project directory, then run npm uninstall bcrypt

4. Next, npm i bcrypt

3. Install MongoDB
  Windows
  1.  For windows follow this instruction: https://docs.mongodb.com/v4.4/tutorial/install-mongodb-on-windows/  
  2.  run MongoDB as a Windows service by typing the following line at the command interpreter with admin previlege: "C:\Program Files\MongoDB\Server\4.4\bin\mongo.exe"

  Mac
  1. For Mac follow this instruction: https://brew.sh/#install
  2. install MongoDB by typing the following lines at the terminal: 
  brew tap mongodb/brew
  brew install mongodb-community@4.4
  run MongoDB as a macOS service by typing the following line at the terminal: brew services start mongodb-community@4.4


4. Open MongoDB and connect to the local server, then create Database Named "Exercise" (Name must match exactly)
  1.  Create a collection named "exercises" (name must match exactly)
  2.  Create a collection named "recipes" (name must match exactly) 
  3.  Create a collection named "sessions" (name must match exactly) 
  4.  Create a collection named "users" (name must match exactly)


5. Run the application by typing in the terminal node app
